{
	NiagaraActor->InitializeEmitterParameters();

	// ...
}
```

This approach has two advantages:

1. Each ability-specific NiagaraActor class holds its own parameters, which reduces the need for maintaining a huge dictionary.
2. You don't need to pass all the parameters collectively. Each ability can handle its parameters and the interaction with the Niagara systems internally, keeping your code organized and easier to maintain in the long run.

